# Constitution

Non-negotiable standards for Playwright work in this repo. Details live in `playwright-conventions.mdc` and skills; this file is the short always-on check.

## MUST

| Rule | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| Role-based locators | `getByRole` / label / text first; testid escape hatch only |
| Web-first assertions | Assert on UI state; Playwright auto-waits — no manual sleeps for readiness |
| `storageState` auth | Login via setup project + `playwright/.auth/user.json`; no per-test UI login |
| Unique self-cleaning data | Unique names per run; every create tears down (see `api-cleanup`) |
| One tag per test | Exactly one of `@smoke` `@sanity` `@regression` `@api` `@e2e` `@destructive` on each `test(...)`; never on `describe` |
| Revert shared mutations | Any test that changes locale/roles/flags/settings restores via `afterEach`/`afterAll` |
| Suite eval before done | Apply `eval-report` skill; update `docs/eval-report.md` before closing a QA task |

## SHOULD

| Rule | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| Faker factories | Happy-path data from `test-data/factories` (Faker); curated invalid in static `.ts` |
| Enums for repeated strings | Shared paths/messages → enums/constants under `test-data/` or `support/` |
| JSDoc on action methods | Document POM action methods (purpose, params, notable waits/side effects) |

## WON'T

| Rule | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| XPath | No `//…` locators |
| `waitForTimeout` | No fixed sleeps |
| Hardcoded secrets | Env / secrets only — never commit credentials |
| `any` | No TypeScript `any` in tests or POMs |
| Weakened assertions | Don't dilute expects to make a red test green |
| Healing a real bug | Real app defects → file a bug; never "fix" the test around them |
| Tags on `describe` | Tags belong on individual tests only |
| Misuse `@destructive` | Not for own-data CRUD that cleans up; only shared/global state mutations |

## Agent governance

Behavioral only — **not** hook-enforced. Audit, then edit.

### Audit-then-edit

1. Read the relevant rules/skills, ticket/AC, and existing code **before** changing files.
2. For every **non-trivial** task, emit a **Proposal** block **before** the first edit:

```markdown
### Proposal
- **Scope:** …
- **Confidence:** N/10
- **Rationale:** …
- **Unknowns:** … (or none)
```

Trivial = typo, comment, or a single-line fix the user already specified exactly. Everything else needs a Proposal.

### Confidence gate

| Confidence | Action |
|------------|--------|
| Below 5 | **Do not proceed.** Ask for the missing input. |
| 5–7 | Proceed only with **explicit Unknowns** listed and **human approval**. |
| 8 or above | Proceed with the Proposal. |

### Never invent

Do **not** invent a path, enum, env var, credential, or user-facing message. **Ask** the user or **explore** the repo/UI (read, MCP, existing factories/enums) instead.

## Index

**Skills** — `api-cleanup` (teardown created data) · `ci-failure-triage` (classify red CI) · `didaxis-program-deleter` (bulk API delete) · `eval-report` (suite reliability metrics → `docs/eval-report.md`) · `explore-and-generate` (coverage gaps, no ticket) · `exploratory-charter` (feature + risk → charter/findings format) · `jira-bug-reporter` (file DS bugs) · `jira-ticket-analyzer` (ticket → Gherkin) · `pom-conventions` (locators in POMs) · `self-heal` (locator drift only)

**Agents** — `test-writer` (plan → spec) · `triage` (red run → bug vs test issue) · `bug-reporter` (confirmed defect → Jira)

**Rules** — `playwright-conventions` (full standards) · `qa-orchestrator` (delegate end-to-end / backlog)
